# Experiment 6-6 Environment Variable Example
#
# Only `--source llm` (LLM-judged battle) requires an API Key;
# simulate / arena / elo / leaderboard / pipeline are all fully offline and require no Key.
#
# Usage: Copy this file as .env and fill in real Keys, or directly `export` into the shell.

# --- Judge Backend 1: Official Anthropic (default priority) ---
# When this Key is present, --judge-backend auto will use the official Anthropic SDK.
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-...

# --- Judge Backend 2: OpenRouter fallback ---
# Used when ANTHROPIC_API_KEY is missing or invalid; uses the OpenAI-compatible SDK pointed at OpenRouter.
# Internal Claude names are automatically mapped to OpenRouter IDs:
#   claude-opus-4-8  -> anthropic/claude-opus-4.8
#   claude-haiku-4-5 -> anthropic/claude-haiku-4.5
#   claude-sonnet-4-6 -> anthropic/claude-sonnet-4.6
# IDs already containing '/' (e.g., openai/gpt-5.6-luna) are passed through as-is.
#
# Force using OpenRouter:
#   python cli.py battle --source llm --judge-backend openrouter \
#     --judge-model claude-opus-4-8 \
#     --candidate-models anthropic/claude-haiku-4.5 openai/gpt-5.6-luna
OPENROUTER_API_KEY=sk-or-...
